# Cursor Guardrails for NeurondB
version: 1
rules:
  - id: general-style
    applies_to:
      - "**/*.c"
      - "**/*.h"
      - "**/*.sql"
    directives:
      - "Always indent with tabs (8-space visual width)."
      - "Keep lines within 80 columns."
      - "Use C-style block comments (/* ... */); never emit // comments."
      - "Prefer defensive checks and explicit error paths."
      - "Place all typedefs, structs, enums, and macros before the first function definition."
      - "Ensure exactly one blank line separates function definitions."

  - id: file-header
    applies_to:
      - "**/*.c"
    header: |
      /*-------------------------------------------------------------------------
       *
       * ${filename}
       *    pgElephant NeurondB module
       *
       * Copyright (c) 2024-2025, pgElephant, Inc.
       *
       * IDENTIFICATION
       *    ${relativePath}
       *
       *-------------------------------------------------------------------------
       */

  - id: review-discipline
    applies_to:
      - "**/*"
    directives:
      - "Run clang-format and clang-tidy when touching C sources."
      - "Do not accept commits that violate style or introduce warnings."
      - "Respect repository-specific build flags and GUC policies."

# Global
Always write C for PostgreSQL extensions. Follow PostgreSQL coding style.
Use tabs for indentation. Line length 80. Variables declared at start of
functions only. Only C-style comments /** */. Minimal comments that say
what, not how. Defensive checks and error paths.

# File templates
When creating a new .c file, start with this header verbatim:

/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------
 *
 * ${filename}
 *    Random Forest implementation for classification and regression
 *
 * Implements Random Forest as an ensemble of decision trees using
 * bootstrap aggregating (bagging) and random feature selection.
 *
 * Copyright (c) 2024-2025, pgElephant, Inc.
 *
 * IDENTIFICATION
 *    ${relativePath}
 *
 *-------------------------------------------------------------------------
 */

